{"id": "EUVD-2025-205106", "enisaUuid": "9877beb1-cdc1-369b-92c8-f3bb006b2144", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nblock: fix memory leak in __blkdev_issue_zero_pages\n\nMove the fatal signal check before bio_alloc() to prevent a memory\nleak when BLKDEV_ZERO_KILLABLE is set and a fatal signal is pending.\n\nPreviously, the bio was allocated before checking for a fatal signal.\nIf a signal was pending, the code would break out of the loop without\nfreeing or chaining the just-allocated bio, causing a memory leak.\n\nThis matches the pattern already used in __blkdev_issue_write_zeroes()\nwhere the signal check precedes the allocation.", "datePublished": "2025-12-24T12:30:29", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-24T12:30:29", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/453e4b0c84d0db1454ff0adf655d91179e6fca3a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7957635c679e8a01147163a3a4a1f16e1210fa03", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7193407bc4457212fa38ec3aff9c640e63a8dbef", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f7e3f852a42d7cd8f1af2c330d9d153e30c8adcf", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-68348"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-68348"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "034c5186-d06a-3380-a18b-0cc0f7291fb5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.63"}, {"id": "0520d3f5-4144-3d7f-aab7-6a758f5707c5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "bf86bcdb40123ee99669ee91b67e023669433a1a <f7e3f852a42d7cd8f1af2c330d9d153e30c8adcf"}, {"id": "0c488b2a-6943-3249-b4ef-2a7979c3a745", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.11"}, {"id": "17de5549-b432-3881-8d7a-a21bef88e626", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "bf86bcdb40123ee99669ee91b67e023669433a1a <7957635c679e8a01147163a3a4a1f16e1210fa03"}, {"id": "58758bdc-6a43-3c06-8b26-bd724e2eae09", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.19-rc1"}, {"id": "677687ac-f96d-381c-a89f-6b70d255aaa1", "pr